%N A393633 Triangle giving the number L(k,n) of paratopy classes of (k X n)-Latin rectangles.
%C A393633 The paratopy class is an equivalence class of Latin rectangles. In addition to the operations of row permutation, column permutation and symbol permutation, under paratopy, the roles of "row", "column" and "symbol" can be permuted (when the dimensions match).
%D A393633 Patric R. J. Östergård and Luka Tolonen, Classifying Equidistant Permutation Codes (in preparation).
%e A393633 Triangle begins:
%e A393633   1;
%e A393633   1, 1;
%e A393633   1, 1, 1;
%e A393633   1, 2, 2, 2;
%e A393633   1, 2, 3, 3, 2;
%e A393633   1, 4, 14, 44, 33, 12;
%e A393633   1, 4, 45, 808, 3712, 1895, 147;
